      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a crucial tool in expanding civil rights and individual liberties in the US, as it allows the courts to strike down laws that infringe on fundamental rights and freedoms. By establishing a right to privacy, reproductive freedom, and equal protection under the law, substantive due process has protected citizens from government overreach and ensured that the Constitution remains a living document. This doctrine has been instrumental in advancing civil rights, particularly for marginalized groups, and has helped to safeguard individual liberties against the tyranny of the majority.",
